Block dimensions: 60 cm × 40 cm × 45 cm. Compute volume: 60*40*45 cm^3 = (60*40=2400; 2400*45=108000) cm^3. Convert to m^3: 108000 cm^3 * (1e-6) = 0.108 m^3.

Mass = density * volume = 2700 kg/m^3 * 0.108 m^3 = 291.6 kg per block.

200 blocks => total mass = 291.6 * 200 = 58320 kg = 58.32 metric tons.

Truck capacity: 8 tons (presumably metric). So number trucks needed = 58.32 / 8 = 7.29 => need 8 trucks.

Answer (B).
